{"id":"rush","term":"Rush","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>The papyrus (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Job 8:11\">Job 8:11</a>). (See BULRUSH.) The expression “branch and rush” in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 9:14\">Isa. 9:14</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 19:15\">19:15</a> means “utterly.”</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Job 8:11","Isaiah 9:14","Isaiah 19:15"]}